comments: Dunn (CHI) establishes himself in a screening position in White's (SAS) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
LaVine (CHI) makes marginal contact with DeRozan (SAS) during the drive, but he does not dislodge him from his legal guarding position.
Satoransky (CHI) makes incidental contact with Mills' (SAS) chin as he makes a natural move toward the basket. Mills initiates the contact by moving into his body.
Poeltl (SAS) makes marginal contact to Young's (CHI) arm as he gathers the rebound, but the contact does not affect his ability to maintain control of the ball.
Young (CHI) slides his pivot foot after gaining possession of the rebound.
White (SAS) maintains a legal guarding position on LaVine (CHI) in the backcourt and cleanly pokes the ball loose twice.  LaVine is unable to get the ball past half-court within 8 seconds.
Mills (SAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Dunn's (CHI) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Dunn (CHI) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by DeRozan (SAS) and cleanly dislodges the ball.
Dunn (CHI) makes contact to DeRozan's (SAS) arm during his dribble, causing the ball to go out of bounds.
Poeltl (SAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Dunn's (CHI) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Poeltl (SAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Hutchison's (CHI) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Mills (SAS) makes marginal contact to Satoransky's (CHI) chest during the inbound, but he does not dislodge him.
Hutchison (CHI) maintains a legal guarding position during the drive and fadeaway shot attempt by DeRozan (SAS).
Poeltl (SAS) makes contact to Young's (CHI) body and arm during his shooting motion that affects his play at the basket.
Forbes (SAS) makes marginal contact to Young's (CHI) arm as he gathers the rebound, but the contact does not affect his ability to maintain control of the ball.
White (SAS) maintains a legal guarding position during the jump shot attempt by LaVine (CHI).
Dunn (CHI) delivers contact to White's (SAS) chest that dislodges him from his legal guarding position.
Dunn (CHI) maintains a legal guarding position on DeRozan (SAS) during the drive and cleanly pokes the ball loose.
LaVine (CHI) briefly places a hand on Gay's (SAS) opposite side hip, but the contact does not affect his ability to get to his spot to set his intended screen.
Poeltl (SAS) makes contact to LaVine's (CHI) arm during his shooting motion that affects his driving shot attempt.
Dunn (CHI) makes contact to DeRozan's (SAS) lower body after his release that affects his ability to follow-through naturally from his jump shot attempt.
